    "sections": {
      "PURPOSE": "3/2CR requires Soldiers to group and zero their individual weapon systems IOT qualify on individual weapon systems and prepare for future combat operations.",
      "MISSION": "3/2CR conducts 25m Group and Zero Range qualify on individual weapon systems and prepare for future combat operations.",
      "END STATE": "All firers complete Table IV (Grouping and Zeroing) IAW with Appendix E, TC 3-20.40\nConcept of the Operation: This OPN will be conducted in III Phases:\nPhase I (Planning & Prep): Begins with identifying personnel to be trained and provide range support and ends when Range Support personnel SP to Range 124 NLT 200700JUL23.",
      "KEY TASKS": "100% accountability of MWE, police call range, range cleared, ammo pickup, and safe movement back to RB.\nService & Support: Class I: A-M-A\nClass V: 5,000 Rounds (AB57), 15 Rounds for Grouping and Zeroing per Firer\nMedical Support: PLT Medics Ammo DO – 200800JUL23/Ammo PU - 211430JUL23",
      "EXECUTION": "): Begins when range support personnel SP to Range 124 and ends when training is complete NLT 211500JUL23.",
      "COMMAND AND SIGNAL": "PACE Plan\nP: 163 (TSM)\nA: 163 (SINGARS)\nC: ATAK (HNC) E: Signal\nCourse of Fire: IAW TC 3-20.40\nUniform: IAW Dragoon Standard\n05JUL23\n10JUL23\n11JUL23\n20-21JUL23\nTBD\n1. Plan the Training\n2. Train/Certify Leader\n3. Recon Training Site\n4. Issue the OPORD\n5. Rehearsal\n6. Exec. the Training\n7. Conduct an AAR\n8. Retrain/Retry\n12JUL23\n21JUL23\n06JUL23\nN\nPersonnel Required: 1x OIC, 1x RSO, 1x Gate Guard, 5x Safeties, 1x Medic, 1x MEV Driver, 1x Ammo NCO, 2x Ammo Detail Equipment Required: Range Box, Engineer Tape, 2x DOS CL I, A8 Targetry, 1x MEV, 10x Barriers\nTimeline: 20JUL23\n0730 – Range Support Arrives\n0800 – Troops Arrive/Ammo Drop\n0845 – Safety Brief\n0900 – Range Wet\n1800 – Range Dry\n2045 – Night Safety Brief\n2100 – Ammo Draw\n2130 – Range Wet\n2300 – Range Dry\nRG124 G&Z CONOP\nFigure 1. Entire Range 124 complex.\nFigure 2. Range 124 firing line. Each lane supports two firers.\n21JUL23\n0800 - Troops Arrives\n0845– Safety Brief\n0900 – Range Wet\n1400 – Range Dry\n1430 – Ammo Pick-up\nNLT 1500 – Range Clear\nFigure 3. Range 124 in GTA."
    },
